				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Atomo wrote:<BR>
<BR>
&gt; I never said I hated this game. I was saying that given the customer service and other BS that we've had to<BR>
&gt; put up with, my chances of ever buying another Verant game are pretty low. <BR>
<BR>
Ah, what do you mean by &quot;my chances&quot;? You make the decision, you don't roll for it. It seems then that you're not so dissatisfied as you let on.<BR>
<BR>
&gt; The only reason alot of us play nowadays is because there is nothing better out there.<BR>
<BR>
So, you seem to suggest that EQ is the pinnacle of the MMORPG genre. If you play because there is nothing else out there then you must be playing because you enjoy it. Hmm, you have many contradictions in what you're saying.<BR>
<BR>
&gt; When I play, it's not to play EverCamp, like you ppl on the carebear servers do.<BR>
<BR>
I play on a &quot;carebear&quot; server, as you call it. Why? Because EQ was not designed with PK primarily in mind. I play the game like it's designed: against the environment. Does this mean I &quot;Evercamp&quot;. No. If people want to camp, fine. You don't have to in the game, and not everyone does as you suggest.<BR>
<BR>
&gt; I can't possibly see the fun in playing on a blue server, where's the thrill? Where's the fun in camping<BR>
&gt; a spawn for 6 hours? <BR>
<BR>
The &quot;fun&quot; is in the new experiences. You reveal your attitude toward gaming when you make the above statements. You think blue servers are only for camping. They are if you have some wayward idea of &quot;completing&quot; an uncompletable game. Perhaps this is why you like PK. You can defeat other players and get that momentary sense of completion.<BR>
<BR>
&gt; And so what if the servers crash the first few weeks? That's to be expected. <BR>
<BR>
Ha! Peeps will raise their discontented voices once again. That's what will happen. And I think you would probably be one of them. ;-)<BR>
<BR>
&gt; I wonder how long it'll be till the next anonymous posters puts up something like &quot;Uh, don't let the door hit<BR>
&gt; you on the way out&quot; and then masturbates wildly to celebrate his comedic genius<BR>
<BR>
No such statement will come from me. I'm just here to point out the incongruities and sweeping generalities in what you say. P <BR>
<BR>
strawman
