			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				*shrug*<BR>
<BR>
Let me explain this to you ppl:<BR>
<BR>
I never said I hated this game. I was saying that given the customer service and other BS that we've had to put up with, my chances of ever buying another Verant game are pretty low. <BR>
<BR>
The only reason alot of us play nowadays is because there is nothing better out there. What do you expect a person to go to, Asheron's Call? <BR>
<BR>
Tallon Zek is pretty close-knit, everyone knows each other pretty well, I'd dare say it's the coolest server in EQ. When I play, it's not to play EverCamp, like you ppl on the carebear servers do. I play to pk. In fact, I've never gone on a planar run or dragon run, and I've only been on one efreeti run. The &quot;L33T&quot; sig is a joke. I can't possibly see the fun in playing on a blue server, where's the thrill? Where's the fun in camping a spawn for 6 hours? That's why we're all moving to SB or AO. I'm already signed up for the AO beta. Just wait and see what happens when those two games come out, EQ's player population will drop like a rock. And so what if the servers crash the first few weeks? That's to be expected. What I hope to NOT see is people like Abashi who pretend to give a damn about pvp servers. SB will be all pvp servers &gt;:)<BR>
<BR>
/rant off<BR>
/flame shield up<BR>
<BR>
I wonder how long it'll be till the next anonymous posters puts up something like &quot;Uh, don't let the door hit you on the way out&quot; and then masturbates wildly to celebrate his comedic genius<BR>

